  "body": "### Description\n\nMany database support replication. \r\nI want to multiple connection for  master (write) / slaves (read)\r\n\r\nCurrently, I create two SessionFactory (write / read )\r\n\r\nif some feature provided, It is more comfortable. \n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n\r\n1. One SessionFactory for Write\r\n2. Multiple SessionFactory for Read (round-robin) or SessionFactoryPool \r\n\r\nif method under `@Transactional`, use Write SessionFactory, \r\notherwise use Read SessionFactoryPool \r\n\r\nor\r\n\r\nAdd explicit readonly method like this \r\n\r\n`SessionFactory.withReadonlySession()` , `SessionFactory.withReadonlyStatelessSession()`",
